article.description: Asha Thomas scored 19 points and Mikayla Cowling had 17 and both hit four 3-pointers to lead No. 21 California to an 82-57 win over Cal Poly on Sunday.
article.headline: No. 21 California women use 3-pointers to top Cal Poly 82-57
article.linkText: No. 21 California women use 3-pointers to top Cal Poly 82-57
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. --  Asha Thomas scored 19 points and Mikayla Cowling had 17 and both hit four 3-pointers to lead No. 21 California to an 82-57 win over Cal Poly on Sunday.

Gabby Green also hit four 3s for 12 points as the Bears (4-0) went 14 of 25 behind the arc. Cal was 8 of 11 on treys in the second half when it shot 61 percent to finish the game at 55 percent (32 of 58).

Beth Balbierz led Cal Poly (2-2) with 14 points and Dynn Leaupepe added 12 but the Mustangs shot just 36 percent after making 6 of 21 from long distance.

Mikayla Cowling's 3-point play highlighted a 10-0 run that gave Cal a 16-7 lead that reached double figures early in the second quarter.  It was 35-16 before the Mustangs scored the last 10 of the half to close within 38-26.
